00:00:00,099 --> 00:00:05,380
A thermodynamic cycle is a sequence of processes
that begins and ends at the same state.

2
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:07,750
A
system has completed a thermodynamic cycle

3
00:00:07,750 --> 00:00:12,269
when the system undergoes a series of processes
and then returns to its original state, so

4
00:00:12,269 --> 00:00:14,860
that the properties of the system at the end
of the cycle

5
00:00:14,860 --> 00:00:16,680
are the same as at its beginning.

6
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:19,960
For example, refrigerant circulating through
a chiller executes

7
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:20,960
a cycle.

8
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:26,820
A vapor compression refrigeration cycle typically
has four processes.

9
00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:32,079
Process 1 to 2 is the Isentropic compression
in a compressor.

10
00:00:32,079 --> 00:00:37,660
Process 2 to 3 is the Constant-pressure
heat rejection in a condenser.

11
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:43,000
Process 3 to 4 is the throttling in an
expansive device.

12
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:49,309
Process 4 to 1 is the Constant-pressure
heat absorption in an evaporator

13
